<FIRST>r a AM-BeatingDeath     11-14 0268</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Beating Death,0278</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Beaten to Death, Husband Arrested</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Sharyn is cq</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By VIRGINIA BYRNE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hotel executive's husband was arrested Monday
and accused of bludgeoning her to death on her 44th birthday with
unopened wine bottles in their luxury apartment.
   ``This was a domestic dispute that escalated into a violent
confrontation,'' said police Deputy Inspector Robert Frankel.
   Allen Cole, 45, was charged with second-degree murder early
Monday, a day after police went to the couple's apartment in lower
Manhattan and found the battered body of his wife, Sharyn, 44, said
Frankel.
   The couple had been married 17 years. Mrs. Cole, a personnel
director with Hilton International, had turned 44 Sunday, the day
she was slain, Frankel said.
   ``There was a lot of blood,'' said detective Sgt. Edward Norris.
``She was very badly beaten.''
   Investigators believe Mrs. Cole was bludgeoned to death with up
to five unopened wine bottles, which were found shattered near her
body.
   ``A wooden meat tenderizer, like a mallet, was found near the
body,'' Frankel added.
   The argument between the couple apparently escalated Sunday
afternoon, when neighbors heard screams coming from the apartment
in Battery Park City near the financial district.
   After the killing, Cole, covered with blood, left the apartment
and stood in the hallway shouting for help, Frankel said. Police
responding to neighbors calls arrived at the apartment.
   The distraught husband, a self-employed food and beverage
consultant, had scratch marks on his face and hands.
   Cole was restrained by police. ``He was visibly upset,'' Frankel
said. ``He didn't want to leave the body.''
</TEXT>
