<HEAD>Foreign Dignitaries Pay Last Respects to Communist Leader</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ambassadors from the Soviet Union and China
today joined a steady stream of people who paid their last respects
to Dolores Ibarruri, a Communist leader from the Spanish Civil War.
   Ibarruri, the daughter of Basque coal miners whose fiery oratory
made her an anti-fascist heroine to millions during the 1936-1939
war, died Sunday in a Madrid hospital at age 93.
