<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   State troopers stormed a southern
Brazil prison today and ended a siege by inmates, killing eight
prisoners and freeing 39 hostages, police said.
   Fifty troopers rushed into the Curitiba prison with guns blazing
after prisoners killed one hostage and injured three others, said
