iron clubs, had demanded machine guns and an armored car for a
getaway.
   The siege began Monday when eight prisoners who worked in the
prison kitchen seized 40 employees, including the director, vice
director and several psychologists, Miller said.
   About 20 other prisoners joined the revolt after the hostages
were taken, Miller said.
   He said negotiations were conducted until early this morning,
when police invaded.
   The prison director, Aldamar Martins Filho, was one of those
injured. He was hospitalized with knife injuries but expected to
survive, Miller said.
   The dead hostage was not immediately identified.
