<HEAD>Museum on How They Escaped Becomes Part Of History</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-East Germany, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MAUREEN JOHNSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Berlin Wall museum featuring a bullet-scarred
van, a makeshift ladder and other poignant reminders of ingenuity
born of desperation has taken on new meaning with the wall's
opening.
   ``We're a real museum now,'' said Horst Schumm, assistant
director of the museum in a converted cafe alongside the wall's
famed Checkpoint Charlie crossing point.
   ``But the museum must stay and we should open in East Germany,
too. It is necessary for all Germans to understand this history and
to learn from it for the future.''
   On Thursday, the museum became part of history in a matter of
hours after East Germany lifted traven its
hemmed-in citizens for the first time since the wall was erected on
Aug. 13, 1961.
   Crossing the wall turned from a death-defying atl restrictions otempt
to escape
into a simple matter of showing an identity card to a border guard.
   For thousands of East Germans who have flocked to the museum,
its exhibits have been a ``surprise and a shock,'' Schumm said.
   ``Some knew from West German television that escapees had been
shot. But in the GDR (East Germany) they'd been told that the
reports were lies from the West and only criminals tried to
escape.''
   He stood beside a little bubble-shaped Isetta car into wchange of $10
in the
price of a bond with a $1,000 face value.
   Yields on three-month Treasury bills fell to 7.93 percent as the
discount lost 2 basis points to 7.68 percent. Yields on six-month
bills fell to 7.83 percent as the discount fell 12 basis points at
7.45 percent. Yields on one-year bills fell to 7.73 percent as the
discount lost 4 basis points to 7.24 percent.
   A basis point is one-hundredth of a percentage point. The yield
is the annualized return on an investment in a Treasury bill. The
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face
value, which is paid at maturity.
   The federal funds rate, the interest on overnight loans between
banks, was quoted by midday at 8 7-16 percent, up from 8] percent
late Monday.
