<HEAD>Bush Urges Caution to Tunisian President in Dealing with Gadhafi</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush urged visiting Tunisian
President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali to use ``caution and reserve'' in
relations with Libya's Moammar Gadhafi, a White House spokesman
said Tuesday.
   Ben Ali told reporters after his Oval Office meeting that he and
Bush ``reviewed peace initiatives for the Middle East.''
   ``I expressed to President Bush our support for the
Palestinian-U.S. dialogue, which we encouraged and which we hope
will lead to a just and lasting peace,'' said Ben Ali, here on a
