   Pelletreau has represented the United States in discussions with
representatives of the Palestine Liberation Organization that began
last year after PLO leader Yasser Arafat renounced terrorism and
acknowledged Israel's right to exist.
   Ben Ali said he and Bush ``discussed regional issues, outlining
recent developments in North Africa, with the creation of the Arab
Maghreb Union.''
   White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said Bush and Ben Ali
``talked generally of the Middle East peace process.''
   ``President Bush expressed his views on Gadhafi, urging caution
and reserve in that area. The president thanked him for hosting the
US-PLO dialogue,'' Fitzwater added.
   Bush also indicated his support for Arab League efforts to bring
peace to Lebanon, the spokesman said.
