<UNK>President Attending Houston Funeral of C. Fred Chambers</UNK>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush will fly to Houston on Thursday
to attend a funeral mass for C. Fred Chambers, a close friend from
their days in the oilfields of Texas.
   Chambers, 71, died Monday. He and Bush met in the early 1950s
when both were young oilmen in Midland, Texas. He became one of
Bush's earliest political boosters and fund-raisers.
   Barbara Bush named her late dog, C. Fred, after Chambers, and
later wrote a whimsical ``autobiography'' about the animal to raise
funds for literacy causes.
   The White House said the president and Mrs. Bush will attend the
funeral at St. Michael's Church in Houston, then return immediately
to Washington.
   Chambers, a retired Navy lieutenant commander, co-founded C&amp;K
Petroleum in Texas in 1953 and remained with the firm until 1981.
   He is survived his wife, Marion, eight children and 18
grandchildren.
