<HEAD>Wilpers Named Executive Editor at Post-Telegram</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John J. Wilpers, former editor-in-chief
of Ingersoll Publications, has been named executive editor at the
Bridgeport Post-Telegram, the newspaper reported Tuesday.
   Wilpers, 39, will assume responsibility for the Post-Telegram's
news operation and editorial staff, effective immediately.
   ``John Wilpers brings to our newspapers one of the most
innovative editorial talents in the industry,'' Post-Telegram
Publisher Dudley B. Thomas said. ``In the weeks and months ahead,
our readers and advertisers can look forward to significant
improvements in our news product.''
   Former Executive Editor Stephen J. Winters will become editor of
the Post-Telegram, a new position.
   Wilpers spent five years with Ingersoll Publications, an
international newspaper group, working with its 41 dailies
including the New Haven Register and more than 200 weekly
newspapers.
   Wilpers also has worked as an editorial writer at The Boston
Globe, education editor and columnist at the Boston Herald and
state editor at The Burlington (Vt.) Free Press.
   ``We will build the Post-Telegram into a paper that readers look
forward to getting and couldn't possibly live without,'' he said.
