<FIRST>r i AM-Korea-US     11-14 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Korea-US,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Soldier Killed, Seven Injured in U.S. Army Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One American soldier and one South
Korean soldier were killed and seven Americans were injured when a
U.S. Army personnel carrier overturned during a training exercise,
the Army said Wednesday.
   An Army statement said the personnel carrier rolled down a slope
Tuesday during manuevers near Camp Casey, north of Seoul. Two
soldiers on the carrier were killed and six were injured in the
accident and a seventh soldier was injured while trying to help
those in the stricken vehicle, it said.
   Officials were investigating the cause of the accident.
   Names of the dead and injured were being withheld pending
notification of next of kin. The carrier belonged to the 4th
Chemical Company of the U.S. 2nd Infantry Division.
   The dead Korean soldier was part of South Korean forces assigned
to U.S. units in South Korea.
   About 43,000 U.S. troops are based in South Korea under a mutual
defense treaty.
</TEXT>
