<SECOND>AM-The '90s-Poll Method, Adv 16,0810</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv16</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Thurs AMs, Nov. 16, and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>Poll on 1990s Has 1,071 Respondents</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-The '90s-Poll</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This Media General-Associated Press poll is
based on telephone interviews Sept. 14-24 with 1,071 adults in the
continental United States. Phone numbers were selected randomly and
interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent
birthday, a random phenomenon.
   The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the
sample. The poll has a 3-point margin of error, meaning that 19 of
20 times its findings should be within 3 points of the result if
every adult American were asked the same questions. The error
margin is larger for subgroups.
   There are other sources of potential error in polls, including
the wording and order of questions. These are the questions in this
poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100:
   1. What do you think will be the most important problem facing
this country 10 years from now? Drugs: 17 percent. Environment: 12
percent. Economy: 9 percent. War: 5 percent. Poverty: 4 percent.
Other answers: 33 percent. Don't know or no answer: 19 percent.
   2. For each of the following issues, please tell me whether you
expect it to get better or worse in the next 10 years, or stay
about the same:
   a. Crime. Better: 14. Worse: 62. Same: 23. DK-NA: 2.
   b. Pollution. Better: 22. Worse: 65. Same: 12. DK-NA: 2.
   c. Drug abuse. Better: 27. Worse: 53. Same: 18. DK-NA: 2.
   d. Education. Better: 58. Worse: 18. Same: 23. DK-NA: 2.
   e. The U.S. economy. Better: 30. Worse: 32. Same: 33. DK-NA: 5.
   f. Your family's financial situation. Better: 56. Worse: 12.
Same: 30. DK-NA: 2.
   g. The federal budget deficit. Better: 21. Worse: 52. Same: 22.
DK-NA: 5.
   h. Ethics in government. Better: 31. Worse: 27. Same: 37. DK-NA:
5.
   i. AIDS. Better: 30. Worse: 57. Same: 8. DK-NA: 5.
   j. Homelessness. Better: 21. Worse: 56. Same: 19. DK-NA: 3.
   k. Race relations in this country. Better: 41. Worse: 27. Same:
29. DK-NA: 3.
   l. International terrorism. Better: 20. Worse: 46. Same: 29.
DK-NA: 5.
   m. World hunger. Better: 17. Worse: 57. Same: 23. DK-NA: 3.
   3. Please tell me if you think each of the following events is
likely or not likely to happen in the next 10 years:
   a. Cancer will be cured. Likely: 42. Unlikely: 54. DK-NA: 4.
   b. AIDS will be cured. Likely: 42. Unlikely: 53. DK-NA: 4.
   c. Cigarette smokers will shrink to a tiny minority. Likely: 59.
Unlikely: 38. DK-NA: 3.
   d. Abortion will be much more restricted than it is today.
Likely: 56. Unlikely: 40. DK-NA: 5.
   e. The United States will put an astronaut on Mars. Likely: 42.
Unlikely: 50. DK-NA: 9.
   f. The United States will become involved in a war. Likely: 43.
Unlikely: 51. DK-NA: 6.
   g. New energy sources will be developed and we will no longer be
dependent on oil. Likely: 49. Unlikely: 45. DK-NA: 6.
   h. Nuclear energy will supply less of our power than it does
now. Likely: 45. Unlikely: 47. DK-NA: 8.
   i. The warming of the Earth's atmosphere because of pollution _
known as the greenhouse effect _ will threaten human survival.
Likely: 48. Unlikely: 45. DK-NA: 6.
   j. The four-day work week will be common in this country.
Likely: 41. Unlikely: 54. DK-NA: 5.
   k. Poverty will be almost eliminated in this country. Likely: 7.
Unlikely: 91. DK-NA: 2.
   l. Racial and religious discrimination in this country will
largely disappear. Likely: 20. Unlikely: 77. DK-NA: 3.
   m. Communism will largely disappear from the world. Likely: 26.
Unlikely: 70. DK-NA: 4.
   n. A Democrat will be elected president. Likely: 72. Unlikely:
18. DK-NA: 11.
   o. A woman will be elected president. Likely: 38. Not likely:
56. DK-NA: 5.
   p. The Republican Party will win control of the Congress.
Likely: 37. Unlikely: 49. DK-NA: 15.
   4. Overall, as you look to the future, do you think life for
people in the United States generally will get better in the next
10 years, or will it get worse? Better: 57. Worse: 28. Stay the
same: 12. DK-NA: 4.
   5. How about your own life _ do you think it will get better in
the next 10 years, or will it get worse? Better: 74. Worse: 10.
Same: 13. DK-NA: 3.
   6. How about life for people in other industrialized nations?
Better: 64. Worse: 16. Same: 10. DK-NA: 10.
   7. How about life for people in developing nations? Better: 60.
Worse: 20. Same: 10. DK-NA: 10.
</TEXT>
