<HEAD>London Shares Close Mixed</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: UPDATES with closing prices</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices finished mixed Tuesday in modest
dealing on London's Stock Exchange, but a key index edged higher
after buyers zeroed in on selected sectors of the market.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index settled 1.5
points, or 0.07 percent, higher at 2,214.7, nearly midway between
its intraday low of 2,206.6 and its best level of the day of
2,223.3.
   Dealers said the market initially recovered from its opening
losses on futures-related buying which boosted the 100-share index
to its session high within the first two hours of trading.
   The index, along with the overall market, was locked in
relatively narrow trading ranges throughout the remainder of the
session.
   Wall Street's choppy opening did little to provide London with
any substantive direction in its late transactions, dealers said.
   The Financial Times 30-share index ended 0.6 points lower at
1,770.8. Volume was a moderate 334.4 million shares traded, higher
than Monday's turnover of 288.5 million shares.
   The Financial Times 500-share index was 1,215.75, down 0.28.
