<FIRST>u f BC-Earns-Penney     11-14 0187</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Penney,0199</SECOND>
<HEAD>J.C. Penney Quarterly Earnings Up 30.5 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   J.C. Penney Co. Inc.'s third quarter earnings
jumped 30.5 percent, the nation's fourth largest retailer reported
Tuesday.
   Net income for the 13 weeks ended Oct. 28 was $209 million, or
$1.52 a share, compared with $160 million, or $1.16 in the
comparable period last year.
   Revenue rose 11.1 percent from $3.73 billion last year to $4.14
billion this year.
   The company said its retail sales climbed 12.5 percent, from
$3.61 billion to $4.06 billion. Other revenue fell from $116
million to $80 million, reflecting Penney's jettisoning of its
casualty insurance business.
   For the first nine-months, net income was $435 million, or $3.17
a share, up 17 percent from $372 million, or $2.73, in the same
period last year.
   Revenue so far this year was $11.06 billion, compared with
$10.35 billion last year.
   Retail sales rose from $10 billion last year to $10.84 billion
this year, while other revenue fell from $351 million to $221
million.
   The nine-month results include a $20 million after-tax charge
from the discontinuing of Telaction, an interactive television
shopping service.
</TEXT>
