<FILEID>AP-NR-11-14-89 2321EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-TBS     11-14 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-TBS,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>Turner Reports Income Rises In Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Turner Broadcasting System Inc. on Tuesday
reported a profit of $35.2 million in the third quarter, up sharply
from a loss of $36.5 million for the same period last year.
   Earnings per share for the quarter ended Sept. 30 totaled to 31
cents, compared with a loss of $1.10 per share in the same period
of 1988.
   TBS reported revenues for the period of $269.3 million, up 36
percent from $198 million in the third quarter of 1988.
   For the first nine months of 1989, TBS reported net income of
$40 million, or 8 cents a share, down from $76.4 million, or $2.54
a share, during the first nine months of 1988.
   TBS Chairman Ted Turner said the increased revenues showed the
company was sound. Company officials attributed part of the rise in
revenue to the addition of Turner Network Television, a cable TV
channel specializing in movies from Turner's MGM and Warner
Brothers film libraries.
</TEXT>
